description:
## Severity
Minor
## Dimension
dry
## Location
src/skills.rs:59-119, src/plugins/mod.rs:644-670
## Violation
Two independent code paths walk the same kind of directory hierarchy with the same conventions (SKILL.md inside a subdir, or .md at the top). Quoted lines:

    // skills.rs
    if path.is_dir() {
        let skill_file = path.join("SKILL.md");
        if skill_file.exists() {
            if let Some(mut skill) = parse_skill_file(&skill_file) {
                ...
            }
        }
    } else if path.extension().and_then(|e| e.to_str()) == Some("md") {
        ...
    }

    // plugins/mod.rs
    let skills_dir = self.path.join("skills");
    if skills_dir.exists() && self.manifest.skills.is_none() {
        if let Ok(entries) = fs::read_dir(&skills_dir) {
            for entry in entries.flatten() {
                if entry.path().is_dir() {
                    self.skill_paths.push(entry.path());
                }
            }
        }
    }

Drift between the two means plugin-provided skills could become discoverable via different rules than directory-installed ones. Plugin skills currently match only directories — not `.md` files — silently dropping skill files the user might expect to work.
## Mandated refactor
Hoist a single `discover_skills_in(dir: &Path) -> Vec<SkillDefinition>` into the skills module and have both Plugin::resolve_skills (after picking up the path candidates) and load_skills call it. Define a single SkillDiscoveryRules struct (allow-bare-md, allow-skill-md-subdir, recursive) and pass it explicitly so the two callers can opt into different rules deliberately rather than by accident.
